<body>
<h1>Chaotic Neutral</h1>
<p class="subtitle">From <a href="http://www.jonnydigital.com/">Jonathan's Reference Pages</a></p>
<hr><!-- ======================================================== -->

<p><a title="Chaotic Neutral"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Chaotic%20Neutral&lastnode_id=592531">Chaotic 
Neutral</a>: It's the <a title="alignment"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=alignment&lastnode_id=592531">alignment</a> 
you play when the <a title="DM"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=DM&lastnode_id=592531">DM</a> 
won't let you be <a title="evil"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=evil&lastnode_id=592531">evil</a>. 
Gather round, folks, as I tell you a story.</p>

<p>My first <a title="foray"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=foray&lastnode_id=592531">foray</a> 
into <a title="Dungeons and Dragons"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Dungeons%20and%20Dragons&lastnode_id=592531">Dungeons 
and Dragons</a> was as a <a title="Dwarven"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Dwarven&lastnode_id=592531">Dwarven</a> 
<a title="Fighter"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Fighter&lastnode_id=592531">Fighter</a>. 
While it was fun at first, the samey <a title="hack-and-slash"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=hack-and-slash&lastnode_id=592531">hack-and-slash</a> 
began to get boring.</p>

<p><b>DM:</b> <a title="Aramil"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Aramil&lastnode_id=592531">Aramil</a>, 
your turn.<br>
<b>Me:</b> Uh, who are we fighting?<br>
<b>DM:</b> Fire giants. Three of them.<br>
<b>Me:</b> How close are they?<br>
<b>DM:</b> Close up. You can hit them with your axe.<br>
<b>Me:</b> Alright. I hit the most wounded one with my axe.  (<i>I take
a few seconds to roll <a title="3d20"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=3d20&lastnode_id=592531">3d20</a> 
for my three attacks and <a title="3d12"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=3d12&lastnode_id=592531">3d12</a> 
for damage, first deciding on <a title="Power Attack"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Power%20Attack&lastnode_id=592531">Power 
Attack</a> for extra damage. Meanwhile, the group waits
patiently.</i>)</p>

<p>Consider this repetitive conversation happening in every single damn <a
title="melee"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=melee&lastnode_id=592531">melee</a> 
of the adventure, and it's understandable that the <a title="DM"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=DM&lastnode_id=592531">DM</a> 
decides to take next week's game off as a <a title="player"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=player&lastnode_id=592531">player</a>. 
<a title="Andrew Common"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Andrew%20Common&lastnode_id=592531">Andy</a> 
is elected to DM this time, while the ex-DM settles into his favoured
role as a <a title="wizard"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=wizard&lastnode_id=592531">wizard</a>. 
Perhaps a better DM could have been chosen than Andy - remembering, of
course, that his character was previously a <a title="Chaotic Neutral"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Chaotic%20Neutral&lastnode_id=592531">Chaotic 
Neutral</a> <a title="Necromancer"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Necromancer&lastnode_id=592531">Necromancer</a> 
who secretly worshipped <a title="Nerull"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Nerull&lastnode_id=592531">Nerull</a>, 
god of Death.</p>

<p>The players are dragged away from their previous roles and choose a
different <a title="class"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=class&lastnode_id=592531">class</a> 
than before. My <a title="fighter"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=fighter&lastnode_id=592531">fighter</a> 
is replaced by a <a title="bard"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=bard&lastnode_id=592531">bard</a>, 
our <a title="cleric"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=cleric&lastnode_id=592531">cleric</a> 
becomes a <a title="sorcerer"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=sorcerer&lastnode_id=592531">sorcerer</a>, 
and the <a title="druid"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=druid&lastnode_id=592531">druid</a>...</p>

<p>The <a title="druid"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=druid&lastnode_id=592531">druid</a>, 
<a title="Nyphur"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Nyphur&lastnode_id=592531">Nyphur</a>, 
elected to remain a <a title="druid"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=druid&lastnode_id=592531">druid</a>. 
Much <a title="coaxing"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=coaxing&lastnode_id=592531">coaxing</a> 
and attacking with empty <a title="coca-cola"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=coca-cola&lastnode_id=592531">coca-cola</a> 
bottles later, he gives in to his new role as a <a title="rogue"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=rogue&lastnode_id=592531">rogue</a>, 
albeit begrudgingly. (It's an interesting side-note that Nyph never used
any of his <a title="rogue"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=rogue&lastnode_id=592531">rogue</a> 
<a title="skills"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=skills&lastnode_id=592531">skills</a>, 
and has never played anything but a <a title="druid"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=druid&lastnode_id=592531">druid</a> 
since.)</p>

<p>Back to the <a title="Chaotic"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Chaotic&lastnode_id=592531">Chaotic</a> 
<a title="Necromancer"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Necromancer&lastnode_id=592531">Necromancer</a>'s 
<a title="campaign"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=campaign&lastnode_id=592531">campaign</a>, 
as it's now referred to, and it's obvious that this adventure is very
different to the last one. Less planned, less <a title="finesse"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=finesse&lastnode_id=592531">finesse</a>... 
more killing of city guards and innocent villagers. My <a title="neutral
good"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=neutral%20good&lastnode_id=592531">neutral 
good</a> elven bard finds it difficult to follow these people in their
<a title="slaughter"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=slaughter&lastnode_id=592531">slaughter</a> 
of all these humans, until they eventually convince me that it's somehow
actually an <a title="evil"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=evil&lastnode_id=592531">evil</a> 
town, full of <a title="evil"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=evil&lastnode_id=592531">evil</a> 
peoples. I join in, realising how rubbish a <a title="bard"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=bard&lastnode_id=592531">bard</a> 
really is in an adventure without <a title="roleplaying"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=roleplaying&lastnode_id=592531">roleplaying</a> 
- not to mention trying to attack <a title="skeletons"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=skeletons&lastnode_id=592531">skeletons</a> 
with a <a title="piercing"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=piercing&lastnode_id=592531">piercing</a> 
weapon like the <a title="rapier"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=rapier&lastnode_id=592531">rapier</a>.</p>

<p>Meanwhile, our <a title="pissed-off"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=pissed-off&lastnode_id=592531">pissed-off</a> 
<a title="rogue"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=rogue&lastnode_id=592531">rogue</a> 
has decided that his character, again <a title="chaotic neutral"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=chaotic%20neutral&lastnode_id=592531">chaotic 
neutral</a>, is filling a house with pints of oil, calling for help and
leaping out the window. After the guards and helpful villagers run in to
assist, our <a title="barbarian"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=barbarian&lastnode_id=592531">barbarian</a> 
holds the door shut and our <a title="wizard"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=wizard&lastnode_id=592531">wizard</a> 
casts <a title="Burning Hands"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Burning%20Hands&lastnode_id=592531">Burning 
Hands</a> into the building.</p>

<p>The supposedly <a title="chaotic neutral"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=chaotic%20neutral&lastnode_id=592531">chaotic 
neutral</a> rogue laughs evilly as the villagers burn to their
collectively untimely deaths. He takes a chew of his own flesh, and the
party leaves to go kill some more stuff for experience.</p>


